# PHP Coding Standards

- Follow PSR-12 Extended Coding Style Guide
- Use type declarations for all function parameters and return types
- Prefer strict types: `declare(strict_types=1);` at the top of PHP files
- Use namespaces for all classes
- Use autoloading via Composer

# PHP Best Practices

- Use dependency injection instead of global state
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3-4 levels)
- Keep functions small and focused (single responsibility)
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use exceptions for error handling, not return codes
- Always validate and sanitize user input
- Use prepared statements for database queries
- Avoid SQL injection by using parameterized queries
- Target PHP 8.3+ features
- Use modern PHP features: typed properties, match expressions, nullsafe operator, etc.
- Avoid deprecated functions and features
- Use early returns to avoid ELSE statements and reduce nesting

# PHP Security

- Never commit sensitive data (passwords, API keys, tokens)
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- Use HTTPS in production
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use CSRF protection for forms
